net.zethmayr.benjamin.spring.common.repository.base

Interface Repository<T,X>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of object persisted
    X - The index type
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    EnumRepository<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EnumMapperRepository, EnumMapperRepository.SingleWired, MapperRepository, MapperRepository.SingleWired

    public interface Repository<T,X>
    A persistent indexed object store over an SQL database table.

      • getFor

        List<T> getFor(X id)
        Retrieves all persisted objects having the given index value. This applies primarily to repositories which are not the primary (inserting) repository for a given table.
        Parameters:
        id - The index value to retrieve for
        Returns:
        A list of persisted objects

      • getAll

      • getUnsafe

        List<T> getUnsafe(String sql,
                  Object... values)
        Executes arbitrary SQL to retrieve objects. Quite possibly a bad idea.
        Parameters:
        sql - SQL which hopefully includes the fields the mapper is looking for
        values - The parameters for the given SQL which hopefully is parameterized
        Returns:
        A list of persisted objects
